OL,6,F"That's why my Bill would require the
OL,7,Fpolice to demonstrate both action and
OL,8,Fmotivation when attempting to
OL,9,Fprosecute in relation to this offence."
OL,11,FAlmost 50 peers are listed to speak
OL,12,Fduring the Bill's second reading on
OL,13,FFriday in the Lords.
OL,15,FChristian Concern chief executive
OL,16,FAndrea Williams urged peers to voice
OL,17,Ftheir opposition to the proposal,
OL,18,Fsaying: "No parliamentarian who cares
OL,19,Fabout parental rights or free speech
OL,20,For human rights should support this
OL,21,FBill."
