OL,6,FIt is convention in the upper house
OL,7,Ffor private members' bills (PMBs),
OL,8,Fwhich are moved by backbench peers, to
OL,9,Freceive an unopposed second reading.
OL,11,FBut plans to wreck the Bill
OL,12,Ftraditionally come to the fore at
OL,13,Fcommittee and report, with amendments
OL,14,Ftabled by those who oppose the
OL,15,Fmeasures.
OL,17,FWithout Government support, PMBs face
OL,18,Fan uphill task to clear all the
OL,19,Frequired parliamentary stages to
OL,20,Fbecome law.
